<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-11424] Endless wait when unhandled exception occurs in camel-olingo</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-11424</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In Olingo2AppImpl.readContent()/writeContent() if a RuntimeError or any other unhandled exception/error occurs the wait for response will never get triggered and the component ends up in an endless wait state.  These functions should be modified to capture any type of throwable/exception/error.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
